\par 
\par \tab Some sacred groves tell a tragic story: The
ir plants have been dug up, trees burned or chopped down, water sources fouled, or standing stones overturned and broken. Perhaps their clearings once served as altars to other priests in the worship of strange gods. Such groves have been defiled, strippe
d of all their powers until druids reclaim them (described below).
\par \tab Other events may result in a still worse fate--a grove becoming cursed. For instance:
